quran[24]{c,v,t}:
  38,65,"Say: 'I am only a warner. There is not any god but God, the One, the Omnipotent"
  38,66,"Lord of the heavens and earth, and of what between them is, the All-mighty, the All-forgiving"
  38,67,"Say: 'It is a mighty tiding"
  38,68,from which you are turning away
  38,69,I had no knowledge of the High Council when they disputed
  38,70,"This alone is revealed to me, that I am only a clear warner"
  38,71,"When thy Lord said to the angels, 'See, I am creating a mortal of a clay"
  38,72,"When I have shaped him, and breathed My spirit in him, fall you down, bowing before him"
  38,73,Then the angels bowed themselves all together
  38,74,"save Iblis; he waxed proud, and was one of the unbelievers"
  38,75,"Said He, 'Iblis, what prevented thee to bow thyself before that I created with My own hands? Hast thou waxed proud, or art thou of the lofty ones"
  38,76,"Said he, 'I am better than he; Thou createdst me of fire, and him Thou createdst of clay"
  38,77,"Said He, 'Then go thou forth hence; thou art accursed"
  38,78,"Upon thee shall rest My curse, till the Day of Doom"
  38,79,"Said he, 'My Lord, respite me till the day they shall be raised"
  38,80,"Said He, 'Thou art among the ones that are respited"
  38,81,until the day of the known time
  38,82,"Said he, 'Now, by Thy glory, I shall pervert them all together"
  38,83,excepting those Thy servants among them that are sincere
  38,84,"Said He, 'This is the truth, and the truth I say"
  38,85,"I shall assuredly fill Gehenna with thee, and with whosoever of them follows thee, all together"
  38,86,"Say: 'I ask of you no wage for it, neither am I of those who take things upon themselves"
  38,87,It is nothing but a reminder unto all beings
  38,88,and you shall surely know its tiding after a while